                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1720.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Chargé
                            <persName type="to">Johnson</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-27T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1915—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram July 22. What recommendation does the Legation make for liquidation
                    of diversions already made and for re-establishment of finances upon sound basis
                    once order is secured? Consult with Receiver and report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
